data: Welcome to the Laboratory for Laser Remote Sensing                       The Laboratory for Laser Remote Sensing is a research facility dedicated to the research and development of laser remote sensing, LIDAR, and laser spectroscopic detection techniques. The laboratory, founded and directed by Dr. Dennis K. Killinger, is located in Tampa, Florida at the University of  South Florida (USF) Physics Department.  If you would like more information on our current research projects, contact Dr. Dennis K.
